rComments: Christina was a nice lady but she was difficult to understand most of the time.  She tries to make you learn by doing lots of demonstrations, but they're really lame and kind of a waste of time. I expected this class to be about astronomy but it was more about physics... it was still easy though especially since the tests were open note, open book.

Christina is a nice lady, her thick accent is hard to understand sometimes.  Teaches straight from the book, also has extra credit opportunities.  I learned very little from this class, but at least she tried with lots of demonstrations and stuff.  Tests are open book, open note also so that was nice.
